This paper deals with a model-based method for fusing data from multiple sensors with a hypothesis-test-based component for rejecting potentially faulty or otherwise malign data. The paper discusses the application of statistical testing frameworks to the Monte Carlo and sensor fusion settings. The paper also presents a synthetic freeway traffic state estimation problem where the filters are able to reject simulated faulty GNSS measurements. Based on this information, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
